## Self-service pipeline

For CNP and CPP platforms, a self-service Azure Pipeline is available in the [`azure-backup-vault`](https://github.com/hmcts/azure-backup-vault) repository. It implements all four restore methods with a PlatOps approval gate and produces a restore-metrics artifact.

| Platform | Pipeline file |
|----------|--------------|
| CNP | `azure-pipelines-restore-vm-cnp.yaml` |
| CPP | `azure-pipelines-restore-vm-cpp.yaml` |

**Key parameters:**

| Parameter | Required | Default | Notes |
|-----------|----------|---------|-------|
| `restoreMethod` | Yes | `method-c` | `method-a` / `method-b` / `method-c` / `method-d` |
| `sourceVmName` | Yes | — | Friendly VM hostname (matches RSV container name) |
| `sourceResourceGroup` | Yes | — | Resource group of the source VM |
| `vaultName` | Yes | — | RSV name |
| `vaultResourceGroup` | Yes | — | RSV resource group |
| `stagingStorageAccount` | Yes (A/B/C) | `cnpvaultrestorationsprod` | Pre-provisioned SA in same region as vault |
| `recoveryPointId` | No | `none` (= latest) | Pin to exact recovery point name |
| `recoveryPointTimeUtc` | No | `none` (= latest) | ISO-8601; selects latest RP at or before this time |
| `targetVmName` | No | auto-generated | Method A only; auto-generates `<sourceVm>-restore-<timestamp>` |
| `targetVnetName` / `targetSubnetName` | Yes (A) | `none` | Target network for new VM |
| `dryRun` | No | `true` | Set to `false` to execute the actual restore |

**How the pipeline works:**

1. **Stage 1 — Preflight:** Authenticates via service connection, lists available recovery points, selects the appropriate one, and prints the restore command that *would* run. No changes made — safe to run at any time.
2. **Stage 2 — Restore:** Blocked by the `vm-restore-platops-approval` ADO environment gate. A PlatOps team member must approve before the restore executes. Sets `dryRun=false` to run a real restore.
3. **Stage 3 — Validate:** Confirms the VM or disks exist post-restore. Skipped if `dryRun=true` or `restoreMethod=method-d`.

A `restore-metrics.json` artifact is published on every run (including dry runs) containing method, source VM, selected recovery point, job ID, status, and duration in minutes.

> **Approval gate setup:** Go to ADO → Environments → `vm-restore-platops-approval` → Approvals and checks → Add approval → set required reviewers to L3 PlatOps on-call. This gate is not in the YAML; it is configured in ADO.

**Measured RTOs (live-tested):**

| Method | Description | Measured RTO (InstantRP) |
|--------|-------------|---------------------------|
| D | ILR — file recovery mount | ~38 seconds |
| B | Restore managed disks only | ~79 seconds (~1 min 19 s) |
| A | Create new VM (AlternateLocation) | ~2 min 15 sec |
| C | Replace existing (OriginalLocation) | ~26 min total (~23 min restore job + stop + start) |

> RTOs measured on Standard_D2ds_v5 in uksouth with InstantRP (snapshot tier, ≤7 days). Vault-tier (>7 days) will be 30–90 min longer.

