## Method D — File Recovery (ILR)

**Use for: S1 (data corruption / ransomware, VM running), S5 (single file loss)**

File Recovery mounts the recovery point as an iSCSI target on a running recovery VM. The source VM remains running and unaffected throughout.

> **Limit:** 12-hour mount session. Large file copies must complete within this window.  
> **Linux:** Python 2.7+ required on the recovery machine.  
> **ADE-encrypted VMs:** not supported — use Method A or B.

### Step 1 — Initiate the file recovery mount

```bash
VaultName="<vault-name>"
VaultRG="<vault-resource-group>"
SourceSubscription="<source-sub-id>"
ItemName="<vm-hostname>"
ContainerName="<container-name>"  # from Prerequisites step 4
RecoveryPointName="<recovery-point-name>"  # from Prerequisites step 4

az account set --subscription $SourceSubscription

az backup restore files mount-rp \
  --resource-group $VaultRG \
  --vault-name $VaultName \
  --container-name $ContainerName \
  --item-name $ItemName \
  --rp-name $RecoveryPointName
```

The output provides a script download URL and connection details. Note the `scriptrunCommand` and `scriptStorageDetails` in the JSON response.

### Step 2 — Run the recovery script on the recovery VM

Download and run the script on a **running VM in the same subscription**:

```bash
# On the recovery machine (Linux):
# Download the script from the URL in the mount-rp output, then:
chmod +x <downloaded-script>.sh
sudo ./<downloaded-script>.sh
```

The script mounts the disks from the recovery point under `/mnt/...`. Browse to the mount point, copy the required files, then proceed to Step 3.

> **Portal alternative:** Go to vault → Backup Items → Azure Virtual Machine → select VM → File Recovery. Download the script from there directly.

### Step 3 — Unmount the recovery point

Once file copy is complete, unmount immediately to release the session:

```bash
az backup restore files unmount-rp \
  --resource-group $VaultRG \
  --vault-name $VaultName \
  --container-name $ContainerName \
  --item-name $ItemName \
  --rp-name $RecoveryPointName
```

