## Method B — Restore Managed Disks (cross-subscription)

**Use for: S4 (clone for staging / DR drill / cross-subscription)**

Restores OS and data disks to a target resource group and generates an ARM deployment template. Use this when you need cross-subscription restore, full configuration control over the recovered VM, or when Method A fails due to SKU unavailability.

This pattern is proven in HMCTS: see the [Atlassian Staging Build runbook](../Services/atlassian-staging-build.html) which restores from prod (`79898897-...`) to staging (`b7d2bd5f-...`).

> **CSR must be enabled** on the source vault — verify in Prerequisites step 2.  
> **Staging storage account must be in the same region as the vault** — no cross-region.  
> **Snapshot-tier:** same-subscription only. For cross-subscription, only vault-tier recovery points work.  
> **VHD staging files:** delete the storage account blobs after the restore completes to avoid cost bleed.

### Step 1 — Restore the disks

```bash
VaultName="<vault-name>"
VaultRG="<vault-resource-group>"
SourceSubscription="<source-sub-id>"
ContainerName="<container-name>"  # from Prerequisites step 4
ItemName="<vm-hostname>"
RecoveryPointName="<recovery-point-name>"

TargetSubscription="<target-sub-id>"
TargetRG="<target-resource-group>"
TargetVMName="<new-vm-name>"
TargetVNet="<target-vnet-name>"
TargetSubnet="<target-subnet-name>"
StorageAccountName="<staging-storage-account-name>"
StorageAccountRG="<storage-account-rg>"  # must be in same region as vault

az account set --subscription $SourceSubscription

az backup restore restore-disks \
  --resource-group $VaultRG \
  --vault-name $VaultName \
  --container-name $ContainerName \
  --item-name $ItemName \
  --rp-name $RecoveryPointName \
  --storage-account $StorageAccountName \
  --restore-to-staging-storage-account true \
  --target-resource-group $TargetRG \
  --target-subscription-id $TargetSubscription \
  --target-vm-name $TargetVMName \
  --target-vnet-name $TargetVNet \
  --target-subnet-name $TargetSubnet \
  --target-vnet-resource-group $TargetRG \
  --storage-account-resource-group $StorageAccountRG \
  --subscription $SourceSubscription
```

Monitor the restore job in the Azure Portal: vault → Backup Jobs. Once the job completes, the disks and an ARM template (`template.json`) appear in the target resource group.

### Step 2 — Deploy the VM from the ARM template

```bash
az account set --subscription $TargetSubscription

# Deploy the VM from the generated ARM template
az deployment group create \
  --resource-group $TargetRG \
  --subscription $TargetSubscription \
  --template-file template.json
```

If you need to customise the VM config (size, NIC, availability zone), edit `template.json` before deploying.

### Step 3 — Clean up staging blobs

Once the VM is running and verified, delete the VHD blobs from the staging storage account to avoid ongoing storage cost:

```bash
az storage blob delete-batch \
  --account-name $StorageAccountName \
  --source <container-name>
```

