## Known limitations

| Limitation | Notes |
|------------|-------|
| Minimum RSV RPO is 4 hours — best achievable with Enhanced policy. ASR would be needed for sub-15-min RPO | Accept and document for each service |
| VMs > 1 TB: RTO may exceed 4 hours even with Instant Restore | No Azure SLA for large VMs. Validate with a test restore before relying on this in an incident |
| Instant Restore (snapshot-tier): same-subscription only | Use vault-tier + CSR for cross-sub; accept slower RTO |
| Method C (Replace Existing): same-subscription only | For cross-sub recovery use Method A or B |
| ADE-encrypted VMs: ILR and Replace Existing not supported | Use Method A/B; add manual file extraction step for file-level scenarios |
| CMK-encrypted VMs: encryption not preserved on restore | Re-apply CMK after restore |
| 9,999 recovery point ceiling per VM — at 6/day this is reached after ~4.6 years | Set retention so older points are pruned before this ceiling is hit |
| Ephemeral OS disk VMs: backup provides no recovery value (disk wiped on reboot) | IaC is the recovery mechanism; exclude these from RSV policy |
| No routine restore testing has been performed on Heritage VMs | Run a test restore against a non-critical VM periodically to validate RTO and process |

> For self-service restores via Azure Pipelines see the [Self-service pipeline](#self-service-pipeline) section above.
